title: My Stroke Story
description: The story of my life before and after stroke
author: Wen

sentences.content: My name is Ronlyn Goo.
I live in Saratoga, California.
I was born in 1962 in San Francisco.
I grew up in Pacifica.
My dad and mom raised me and my two younger sisters, Jaylynne and Stacy.
I studied Chemical Engineering at UC Berkeley.
I met Wen Eng, a fellow chemical engineering major.
I graduated in 1985.
I worked at Dow Chemical after college.
I started as a process engineer.
My last position was in research and product development.
Then I went to Stanford GSB for an MBA.
After Stanford, I was a management consultant at CSC Index.
I ran my own consulting company Proquest Systems after that.
I also led a Center for Innovation for Mission College.
I have been married to my spouse for 30 years.
Wen and I met in college.
We have two children, David and Robert.
David is 27 years old.
Robert is 25 years old.
David went to Stanford.
He earned bachelor and master degrees in computer science.
Then, he founded a technology company called Bunker Hill Health in Palo Alto.
Robert went to Caltech.
He majored in computer science and history.
He works for a machine learning startup in San Francisco.
I was a CEO presenting to my board when I had my stroke.
I had a severe hemorrhagic stroke in September 2015.
About 13% of stroke survivors were like me.
About one out of three died within 30 days.
About 25% survive five years
I was initially in a coma for a week.
I woke with right side impairment and severe aphasia.
I could only speak one word: “after”.
I spent a month in the hospital, then a month in the stroke recovery ward.
Then I had transitional rehab at home followed by nearly 400 out-patient therapy sessions.
I feel lucky because more than one third of hemorrhagic stroke victims do not live passed the first few days and up to two thirds do not live a year after stroke.
I also attend SPARC at San Jose State twice a week.
On Wednesdays, we discuss news as a group.
On Fridays, we have group discussions and choir.
I also attend ATP at Cal State East Bay. On Mondays, We discuss National Parks like Yosemite and cooking.
On Wednesdays, I sing.
Tuesdays and Thursdays, we exercise together.
On Fridays, I sing in the choir.
I attend Aphasia Recovery Connection & Lingraphica coffee talk, travel, I Love the Beatles and Aplasia Running Club.
I attend speech therapy at Brooklyn College.
Mondays are individual sessions.
Wednesdays, we sing.
In Speech Recovery Pathways, we have a group discussion called "Let's Talk."
We also read the book Water for Elephants.
I attend Voices of Hope for Aphasia.
We played “Name That Song”, we read Where the Crawdads Sing for our book club.
We also partipated in art, writing, chat and exercise groups.
I attend Nova Southeastern and discuss stories with others.
I walk around the park near my home.
I walk up to ten laps in an hour.
I ride my recumbent tricycle.
I read (listen to) books using audible.
Where the Crawdads Sing by Delia Owens
The Nightingale by Kristin Hannah
Water for Elephants by Sara Gruen.
I enjoy painting in watercolors.
I started with plants.
Now, I am trying to paint animals like elephants, giraffes, tigers, lions and zebras.
I bake desserts.
I am gardening.
I like growing plants from seeds.
I like the Golden State Warriors, especially Steph Curry.
I like the San Francisco 49ers.
I especially like Nick Bosa, George Kittle and Deebo Samuel.
Since my stroke, I travelled to Hawaii and up and down the west coast.
I have been to Seattle, Portland, Eugene, San Francisco, Santa Barbara, Los Angeles, and San Diego.
I have a weekly chat with Sherry, Theresa, Janet, Doreen, Cindy and others.
I am trying my hardest to get better!!!
